n's outfits\", \"from\": 8899, \"to\": 8918}, {\"ngram\": \"the neck ties\", \"from\": 8948, \"to\": 8961}, {\"ngram\": \"the top buttons\", \"from\": 8966, \"to\": 8981}, {\"ngram\": \"the shirts\", \"from\": 8985, \"to\": 8995}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But there is no coming back from those jeans.\", \"from\": 8997, \"to\": 9042, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"those jeans\", \"from\": 9030, \"to\": 9041}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As a user commented on X: \\\"It's giving yeehaw mixed with flight attendant.\\\"\", \"from\": 9044, \"to\": 9119, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a user\", \"from\": 9047, \"to\": 9053}, {\"ngram\": \"X\", \"from\": 9067, \"to\": 9068}, {\"ngram\": \"yeehaw\", \"from\": 9083, \"to\": 9089}, {\"ngram\": \"flight attendant\", \"from\": 9101, \"to\": 9117}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the last few Olympic Games, including Tokyo 2020, Team Singapore has usually worn a uniform comprising a red jacket and light-coloured trousers.\", \"from\": 9121, \"to\": 9269, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9180, \"end\": 9189, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.621120534357369e-24, \"text\": \"Singapore\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the last few Olympic Games\", \"from\": 9125, \"to\": 9151}, {\"ngram\": \"Tokyo\", \"from\": 9163, \"to\": 9168}, {\"ngram\": \"a uniform\", \"from\": 9207, \"to\": 9216}, {\"ngram\": \"a red jacket\", \"from\": 9228, \"to\": 9240}, {\"ngram\": \"light-coloured trousers\", \"from\": 9245, \"to\": 9268}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PHOTO: SNOC/KONG CHONG YEW Team Singapore has mostly stuck to a core uniform of a red jacket and light-coloured trousers for the last few Olympics Games, including Tokyo 2020.\", \"from\": 9271, \"to\": 9447, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9304, \"end\": 9313, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.621120534357369e-24, \"text\": \"Singapore\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\"}, {\"begin\": 9436, \"end\": 9441, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.8229437680557001, \"rank\": 0.21514985447662074, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"PHOTO\", \"from\": 9271, \"to\": 9276}, {\"ngram\": \"a core uniform\", \"from\": 9333, \"to\": 9347}, {\"ngram\": \"a red jacket\", \"from\": 9351, \"to\": 9363}, {\"ngram\": \"light-coloured trousers\", \"from\": 9368, \"to\": 9391}, {\"ngram\": \"the last few Olympics Games\", \"from\": 9396, \"to\": 9423}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There have been minor variations via the use of accessories such as scarves, though in 2000, there was a small change-up with female athletes wearing all-beige outfits.\", \"from\": 9449, \"to\": 9617, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"minor variations\", \"from\": 9465, \"to\": 9481}, {\"ngram\": \"the use\", \"from\": 9486, \"to\": 9493}, {\"ngram\": \"accessories\", \"from\": 9497, \"to\": 9508}, {\"ngram\": \"scarves\", \"from\": 9517, \"to\": 9524}, {\"ngram\": \"a small change-up\", \"from\": 9552, \"to\": 9569}, {\"ngram\": \"female athletes\", \"from\": 9575, \"to\": 9590}, {\"ngram\": \"all-beige outfits\", \"from\": 9599, \"to\": 9616}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As Mr Chris Chan, secretary-general of the Singapore National Olympic Council (SNOC), told ST in 2012: \\\"Prior to 1973, our national sportsmen wore an all-beige ensemble for formal dress.\", \"from\": 9619, \"to\": 9805, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9631, \"end\": 9635, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jackie_Chan\", \"score\": 0.9999999987785486, \"rank\": 1.1698535788852483e-09, \"text\": \"Chan\", \"types\": [],